.The Hydrid model using the well developed

x4freetext: The overall error for the cross section (and yield)
measurements was estimated to be 20%. It is mainly due
to errors in counting statistics, absolute efficiency
calibration curve of the Ge(LI) detector,target foil
times,proton-beam energy loss and the error associated
with the Al monitor excitation function.
